name: IAM (4-byte)*
desc: E31-KCA = (KA (max) map value * IAM) + FBKC + FLKC. Total Timing = KCA + base timing + timing compensations

name: Engine Load (4-Byte)*
desc: E32-This is the current engine load (g/rev) as determined by the ECU.

name: CL/OL Fueling*
desc: E33-Fuel system status. [8 = CL (normal)][10 = OL (normal)][7 = OL insufficient ECT][14 = OL due to system failure]

name: Turbo Dynamics Integral (4-byte)*
desc: E34-Current WG duty corr (ABS) applied by the Turbo Dynamics Integral tables to achieve target boost. Can be Cumulative

name: Boost Error*
desc: E35-Difference between target boost (post-compensations) and actual boost (target boost - actual boost)

name: Target Boost (4-byte)*
desc: E36-Current boost target as determined by the Target Boost table(s). This includes any compensation, if applicable.

name: Turbo Dynamics Proportional (4-byte)*
desc: E37-Current WG duty correction (absolute) that is being applied by the Turbo Dynamics Proportional table.

name: Throttle Plate Opening Angle (4-byte)*
desc: E38-Actual throttle plate opening percentage. More accurate than the standard Throttle Opening Angle % SSM parameter.

name: Feedback Knock Correction (4-byte)*
desc: E39-This is the temporary negative correction to timing advance in response to what the ECU perceives as knock.

name: Fine Learning Knock Correction (4-byte)*
desc: E41-Current learned correction that is being applied which is stored and applied across specific load and rpm ranges.

name: Map Ratio (Primary)*
desc: E42-The ratio used to determine the portion of specific multiple maps which are combined to determine the target value.

name: A/F Learning #1 A (Stored)*
desc: E44-A/F learned correction to CL and OL fueling across specific air flow ranges based on short-term A/F Correction witin range.

name: A/F Learning #1 B (Stored)*
desc: E45-A/F learned correction to CL and OL fueling across specific air flow ranges based on short-term A/F Correction witin range.

name: A/F Learning #1 C (Stored)*
desc: E46-A/F learned correction to CL and OL fueling across specific air flow ranges based on short-term A/F Correction witin range.

name: A/F Learning #1 D (Stored)*
desc: E47-A/F learned correction to CL and OL fueling across specific air flow ranges based on short-term A/F Correction witin range.

name: A/F Learning #1 (4-byte)*
desc: E48-Current A/F Learning being applied. Higher resolution then the standard SSM A/F Learning #1 parameter.

name: Idle Speed Map Selection*
desc: E49-Current Idle Speed Target MAP being used. 3 table ROM->[1=A],[2=B],[4=C]. 4 table ROM->[1=A],[2=B],[3=C],[4=D]

name: Fuel Injector #1 Latency (4-byte)*
desc: E50-Current injector latency as determined by the Injector Latency table.

name: Manifold Absolute Pressure (4-byte)*
desc: E51-MAP is limited to about 37 psi absolute (about 22 psig at sea level). This parameter has no effective limit.

name: Manifold Relative Sea Level Pressure (4-byte)*
desc: E52-Same as Manifold Absolute Pressure (Direct) except represented as relative pressure with the assumption of sea level.

name: Ignition Base Timing*
desc: E53-Current base ignition timing as determined by the Base Timing tables.

name: Tip-in Throttle*
desc: E54-This is the current throttle angle change % used as an input by the Throttle Tip-in Enrichment table.

name: Tip-in Enrichment (Last Calculated)*
desc: E55-Current (or last) calculated tip-in enrichment value. The value is  not cleared, effectively shows the last calculated value.

name: Requested Torque*
desc: E56-Current requested torque which is used as an input to the Target Throttle Plate Position (Requested Torque) table.

name: Target Throttle Plate Position*
desc: E57-Current target throttle plate position as determined by the Target Throttle Plate Position (Requested Torque) table.

name: Fine Learning Table Offset*
desc: E58-Current index position for the Fine Learning Knock Correction table being applied (and potentially adjusted), stored in ram.

name: Gear (Calculated)*
desc: E59-Current manual transmission gear selection as estimated by the ECU based on vehicle speed and RPM.

name: Fuel Injector #1 Pulse Width (4-byte)*
desc: E60-Fuel Injector #1 PW with higher resolution. Note: This parameter does not include latency unlike the standard parameter.

name: A/F Learning Airflow Range (Current)*
desc: E61-Current stored A/F Learning index position. A value of 1-4 corresponds to airflow ranges A-D respectively.

name: Primary Wastegate Duty Maximum* (4-byte)*
desc: E70-Current max WG duty as determined by the Max Wastegate Duty table(s) with all WG compensations applied.

name: Primary Wastegate Duty Maximum* (4-byte)*
desc: E77-Current max WG duty as determined by the Max Wastegate Duty table(s) with all WG compensations applied.

name: A/F Correction #1 (4-byte)*
desc: E81-A higher precision alternative to the standard SSM A/F Correction #1 parameter.

name: Primary Open Loop Map Enrichment (4-byte)*
desc: E84-Primary enrichment value based on the Primary Open Loop Fueling table(s) Note: this value is NOT the final fueling target.

name: A/F Sensor #1 (4-byte)*
desc: E91-A higher precision alternative to the standard SSM A/F Sensor #1 (AFR/lambda) parameter.

name: Manifold Relative Pressure (4-byte)*
desc: E113-Actual relative boost pressure and therefore will match a boost gauge regardless of local atmospheric pressure. No limit.

name: Primary Enrichment Final (4-byte)*
desc: E115-This is the Primary Open Loop Map Enrichment value with the minimum warm-up enrichment factors applied. Not Final.

name: Knock Correction Advance Primary Map Ratio*
desc: E116-Knock Correction Advance Primary Map Ratio

name: Map Ratio (Alternate)*
desc: E117-The ratio used to determine the portion of specific Alternate multiple maps which are combined to determine the target value.

name: Closed Loop Fueling Target (4-byte)*
desc: E121-This is the closed loop fueling lambda target which is used in determining short-term corrections (A/F Correction #1).

name: Final Fueling Base (4-byte)*
desc: E123-This is the final fueling multiplier after corrections are applied but before per injector compensation.

name: Manifold Absolute Pressure
desc: P7-Pressure value calculated from the manifold absolute pressure sensor (absolute value)

name: Knock Correction Advance
desc: P23-Retard amount when knocking has occurred. Partial learned value of the learned ignition timing.

name: Manifold Relative Pressure
desc: P25-Manifold Absolute Pressure [P7] minus current Atmospheric Pressure [P24].

name: Engine Load (Calculated)
desc: P200-Engine load as calculated from MAF and RPM.

name: Injector Duty Cycle
desc: P201-IDC as calculated from RPM and injector PW.

name: Manifold Relative Pressure (Corrected)
desc: P202-Difference between Manifold Absolute Pressure and Atmospheric Pressure.

name: Fuel Consumption (Est.)
desc: P203-Estimated fuel consumption based on MAF, AFR and vehicle speed.

name: Global Timing User Adjustment Value
desc: P239-This is the fixed amount of timing removed globally - set by the user

name: Engine Idle Speed User Adjustment (A/C off)
desc: P240-This is the fixed amount of idle speed adjustmnet while the A/C is off - set by the user

name: Engine Idle Speed User Adjustment (A/C on)
desc: P241-This is the fixed amount of idle speed adjustmnet while the A/C is on - set by the user
